def get_decade(year):
    if 1989 <= year <= 1999:
        return '1990s'
    elif 2000 <= year <= 2009:
        return '2000s'
    elif 2010 <= year <= 2019:
        return '2010s'
    elif 2020 <= year <= 2029:
        return '2020s'
    else:
        return 'Other'


dfr_clean['decade'] = dfr_clean['Year'].apply(get_decade)

def visualize_features(data,
                       discrete_features,
                       nominal_categorical_features,
                       binary_features,
                       ordinal_features,
                       temporal_features,
                       continuous_features):
    def remove_unused_axes(fig,axes,used_axes_count):
        for i in range(used_axes_count,len(axes)): 
            fig.delaxes(axes[i])
    def create_subplots(figures, n_col=3):
        n_rows=math.ceil(len(figures)/n_col)
        fig,axes=plt.subplots(n_rows,n_col,figsize=(6*n_col, 3*n_rows))
        axes=axes.flatten() if isinstance(axes,np.ndarray) else [axes]
        return fig,axes    
        
    if discrete_features:
        fig, axes=create_subplots(discrete_features)
        for i, col in enumerate(discrete_features):
            sns.histplot(data[col], kde=False,ax=axes[i], color='skyblue', bins=10)
            axes[i].set_title(f'Histogram of {col}(Discrete)', fontsize=10)
            axes[i].set_xlabel(col, fontsize=10)
            axes[i].set_ylabel('frequency', fontsize=10)

def get_top_category_combinations(data,category_list,top_n=5):
    result={}
    years=data['Year'].unique()
    for year in sorted(years):
        data_year=data[data['Year']==year]
        group_counts=data_year.groupby(category_list).size().reset_index(name='count')
        top_combinations=group_counts.sort_values('count',ascending=False).head(top_n)
        result[year]=top_combinations
    return result

    'Articulated Truck Involvement':{'No':0,'Yes':1},
    'Christmas Period':{'No':0,'Yes':1},
    'Easter Period':{'No':0,'Yes':1},

    'Time of day':{'Day':1,'Night':0},

}
print("\n--- Inspecting Binary Features ---")
for feature in binary_features:
    if feature in dfr_clean.columns:
        unique_vals = dfr_clean[feature].dropna().unique()
        print(f"Unique values in '{feature}': {unique_vals}")
    else:
        print(f"Feature '{feature}' not found in DataFrame.")

print("\n--- Applying Binary Mappings ---")
for feature, mapping in binary_mappings.items():
    if feature in dfr_clean.columns:
        dfr_clean[feature] = dfr_clean[feature].map(mapping)
        if dfr_clean[feature].isnull().any():
            unmapped_vals = dfr_clean.loc[dfr_clean[feature].isnull(), feature].unique()
            print(f"Warning: Feature '{feature}' contains unmapped values: {unmapped_vals}")
            dfr_clean[feature].fillna(0, inplace=True)
            print(f"Filled NaNs in '{feature}' with 0.")
    else:
        print(f"Feature '{feature}' not found in DataFrame.")
print("\n---verifying binary Features---")
for feature in binary_features:
     if feature in dfr_clean.columns and dfr_clean[feature].isnull().any():   
         print(f"\n warning:Feature '{feature}'contain Nan values after mapping")
         dfr_clean[feature].fillna(0,inplace=True)
     else:
         print(f"Feature '{feature}'mapped successfully with no Nans")      
print(f"\n---applying temporal Feature----")
if 'DateTime' in dfr_clean.columns:
    dfr_clean['DateTime']=pd.to_datetime(dfr_clean['DateTime'],errors='coerce')

    dfr_clean['Month']=dfr_clean['DateTime'].dt.month
    dfr_clean['Hour']=dfr_clean['DateTime'].dt.hour
    dfr_clean['Dayweek']=dfr_clean['DateTime'].dt.dayofweek
    dfr_clean['isweekend']=dfr_clean['Dayweek'].apply(lambda x:1 if x>5 else 0)
    print("Temporal Feature are extracted Successfully")
else:
    print("Error: 'DateTime' column not founf in DataFrame")

for feature in discrete_features:

def map_year_to_decade(year):
    if 1990 <= year <= 1999:
        return '1990s'
    elif 2000 <= year <= 2009:
        return '2000s'
    elif 2010 <= year <= 2019:
        return '2010s'
    elif 2020 <= year <= 2029:
        return '2020s'
    else:
        return np.nan                
if 'Year' in dfr_clean.columns:
    dfr_clean['Decade'] = dfr_clean['Year'].apply(map_year_to_decade)
    print("'Decade' column successfully created.")
else:
    print("Error: 'Year' column does not exist in DataFrame.")
if 'Decade' in dfr_clean.columns:
    unmapped_decades = dfr_clean['Decade'].isnull().sum()
    print(f"Number of records with unmapped decades: {unmapped_decades}")              
    if unmapped_decades > 0:
        dfr_clean = dfr_clean.dropna(subset=['Decade'])
        print("Dropped records with unmapped decades.")
    else:
        print("All records mapped to a decade.")         
else:
    print("'Decade' column is missing. Skipping mapping.")

def assign_population(row):
    decade = row['Decade']
    if decade == '1990s':
        return row.get('pop_1990s', np.nan)
    elif decade == '2000s':
        return row.get('pop_2000s', np.nan)
    elif decade == '2010s':
        return row.get('pop_2010s', np.nan)
    elif decade == '2020s':
        return row.get('pop_2020s', np.nan)
    else:
        return np.nan

print("\n--- Assigning Population Based on Decade ---")

def assign_population(row):
    decade = row['Decade']
    if decade == '1990s':
        return row.get('pop_1990s', np.nan)
    elif decade == '2000s':
        return row.get('pop_2000s', np.nan)
    elif decade == '2010s':
        return row.get('pop_2010s', np.nan)
    elif decade == '2020s':
        return row.get('pop_2020s', np.nan)
    else:
        return np.nan
